Calophyllum apetalum

    Authority   Willd.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Guttiferales:Guttiferae
     Synonyms
   Common names coachwood
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4073

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Rashid M 1975 pp 223-227 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, PH, LIG, USE]
   KILLING T
   Resistant to below 4Â°C.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial evergreen tree. (GMIN and GMAX estimated by the compiler).
   COMMON NAMES
   Poon, Sarpuna, Irai, Holohonne, Kullponne, Kiri-honne, Kalpoon,
   Cherupinnai, Attupunna, Manjapunna, Cherupunna, Purapunna, Bobbi,
   Sirubinnai, Sirapunna, Cheru-pinnay, Siriponne.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms; C. wightianum, C. decipiens. The relative humidity
   should be 80-100% in July and 60-80% in January. Poon can be found at
   elevations between sea level and 1370 m. The tree can reach a height of
   up to 20 m. The tree is native of south western India. It prefers very
   moist situations with running water, but will not withstand stagnant
   water.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
